{"title_page": "Puri Jagannadh", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian film director, screen writer and producer}}\n{{Hatnote|This is a [[Telugu language|Telugu name]]; the family name is Petla.}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Puri Jagannadh\n| image = Purijagannadh.jpg\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1966|9|28}}\n| birth_place = Bapiraju Kothapalli, [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[India]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070202012250/http://www.cinegoer.com/puri1.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=2 February 2007|title=CineGoer.com - Interview With Puri Jagannath|accessdate=25 March 2017}}</ref>\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| othername = Jagan and Puri<ref name=\"M. L. Narasimham\">{{cite news |last1=M. L |first1=Narasimham |title=In a dual role |url=https://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/mp/2002/07/23/stories/2002072300260400.htm |newspaper=The Hindu |accessdate=13 December 2018|date=23 July 2002 }}</ref>\n| yearsactive = 2000\u2013present\n| occupation = {{hlist|Director|producer|screenwriter}}\n| spouse = Lavanya\n| children = Akash<br>Pavitra\n| relatives = [[Sairam Shankar]] (brother)<br>[[Petla Uma Sankara Ganesh]](brother)\n| partner = \n| parents = \n| residence = [[Hyderabad]], [[Telangana]]\n| website = {{url|purijagan.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Puri Jagannath'''<ref>[https://archive.is/20130629122208/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-04-23/news-interviews/29465896_1_puri-jagannath-charmme-films Yes, I was in depression: Puri Jagannath \u2013 Times Of India]. Articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com (23 April 2011). Retrieved on 15 February 2014.</ref> (born 28 September 1966) is an [[Indian film]] [[Film director|director]], screenwriter and [[Film producer|producer]], who works primarily in the [[Telugu cinema]]. He is known as the ''Dynamic Director'' in Telugu film industry for his characterizations and style of film making.\n\nHe made his debut with the 2000 blockbuster film ''[[Badri (2000 film)|Badri]]'' starring [[Pawan Kalyan]], [[Renu Desai]] and [[Ameesha Patel]]. In 2006, he directed ''[[Pokiri (2006 film)|Pokiri]]'', premiered at the [[7th IIFA Awards|7th IIFA Film Festival]] held in [[Dubai]]. The film was later re-made into several Indian Languages, and catapulted Puri to national recognition.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archives.chennaionline.com/film/Events/2006/06iifa.asp|archive-url=https://archive.is/20090113130322/http://archives.chennaionline.com/film/Events/2006/06iifa.asp|url-status=dead|archive-date=13 January 2009|title=IIFA to showcase South films in Dubai|date=13 January 2009|accessdate=25 March 2017}}</ref> \nHe made his [[Bollywood]] debut in 2004, with the film [[Shart: The Challenge]]. In 2011, he directed ''[[Bbuddah... Hoga Terra Baap]]'', which was archived in the [[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences|Oscar]] library.<ref>[http://in.news.yahoo.com/oscar-academy-asks-big-b-bbuddah-script-133733464.html Oscar Academy asks Big B for 'Bbuddah...' script \u2013 Yahoo! News India] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160314210829/http://in.news.yahoo.com/oscar-academy-asks-big-b-bbuddah-script-133733464.html |date=14 March 2016 }}. In.news.yahoo.com (29 July 2011). Retrieved on 15 February 2014.</ref>\n\nHe produces films under his [[Production company|production companies]], [[Puri Jagannadh Touring Talkies]] and [[Vaishno Academy]]. He also owns a [[Record label|music company]] called as [[Puri Sangeet]].<ref>[http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article2153181.ece Arts / Cinema : Fanboy Bachchanalia] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110906014623/http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article2153181.ece |date=6 September 2011 }}. The Hindu (2 July 2011). Retrieved on 15 February 2014.</ref> Other box office hits that he directed include, ''[[Badri (2000 film)|Badri]],''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://in.bookmyshow.com/person/puri-jagannadh/1745|title=Puri Jagannadh - Movies, Biography, News, Age & Photos {{!}} BookMyShow|website=BookMyShow|access-date=3 August 2017}}</ref> ''[[Itlu Sravani Subramanyam]], [[Appu (2002 film)|Appu]], [[Idiot (2002 film)|Idiot]], [[Amma Nanna O Tamila Ammayi]], [[Shivamani (film)|Sivamani]], [[Bujjigadu]], [[Pokiri]], [[Desamuduru]], [[Neninthe]], [[Golimaar (film)|Golimaar]], [[Businessman (film)|Businessman]], [[Iddarammayilatho]], [[Heart Attack (2014 film)|Heart Attack]] and [[Temper (film)|Temper]]''.\n\n== Biography ==\nPuri Jagannath was born in a [[Telugu language|Telugu]]-speaking [[Hindu]] [[Koppula Velama]] family in [[Pithapuram]], [[East Godavari]] District of [[Andhra Pradesh]]. His native village is Bapiraju Kothapalli, Kotauratla Mandal, [[Visakhapatnam District]] in Andhra Pradesh. He studied at St. Theresa R.C.M. high school in Pedaboddepalli. ''Petla'' is his family name, ''Puri Jagannath'' is his given name, which is in honor of the [[Jagannath Temple, Puri|Lord Jagannath Temple of Puri]]. He started his career as an assistant director to [[Ram Gopal Varma]] for several [[Telugu films]].<ref>[http://entertainment.oneindia.in/telugu/news/2009/krishnavamsi-puri-jagannath-films-091009.html It\u2019s Krishnavamsi versus Puri Jagannath this week] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131002101044/http://entertainment.oneindia.in/telugu/news/2009/krishnavamsi-puri-jagannath-films-091009.html |date=2 October 2013 }}. Entertainment.oneindia.in (9 October 2009). Retrieved on 15 February 2014.</ref> His Telugu directorial debut, ''[[Badri (2000 film)|Badri]]'', starred [[Pawan Kalyan]]. He is a good friend to actor [[Ravi Teja]] who starred in some of his films like ''[[Itlu Sravani Subramanyam]]'', ''[[Idiot (2002 film)|Idiot]]''. He has also worked in the Kannada industry and introduced [[Puneeth Rajkumar]]. In 2011 he worked with [[Amitabh Bachchan]].<ref>[http://www.totaltollywood.com/interviews/Raviteja_2017.html Raviteja \u2013 Interviews in Telugu Movies] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120107033006/http://www.totaltollywood.com/interviews/Raviteja_2017.html |date=7 January 2012 }}. Totaltollywood.com. Retrieved on 15 February 2014.</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:33px;\"| #\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:33px;\"| Year\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:225px;\"| Film\n! colspan=\"5\" | Credited as\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:100px;\"| Language\n! rowspan=\"2\"  style=\"text-align:center; width:250px;\"| Notes\n|-\n! width=65 | [[Film director|Director]]\n! width=65 | [[Film producer|Producer]]\n! width=65 | [[Screenwriter|Story]]\n! width=65 | [[Screenplay]]\n! width=65 | [[Dialogues]]\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n||1\n|| 2000\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| ''[[Badri (2000 film)|Badri]]''\n| {{Yes}}\n|\n| {{Yes}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n||2\n|| 2000\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| ''[[Bachi (Film)|Bachi]]''\n| {{Yes}}\n|\n| {{Yes}}\n| {{Yes}}\n|\n| Telugu\n|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n||3\n|| 2001\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| ''[[Yuvaraja (film)|Yuvaraja]]''\n| {{Yes}}\n| \n|\n|\n|\n| [[Kannada]]\n| Remake of Telugu film [[Thammudu (film)|Thammudu]] with [[Shiva Rajkumar]]\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n||4\n|| 2001\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| ''[[Itlu Sravani Subramanyam]]''\n| {{Yes}}\n|\n| {{Yes}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| Telugu\n|\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n||5\n|| 2002\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| ''[[Appu (2002 film)|Appu]]''\n| {{Yes}}\n|\n| {{Yes}}\n| {{Yes}}\n|\n| Kannada\n|Introduced [[Puneeth Rajkumar]] in [[Rajkumar (actor)|Rajkumar]] banner.\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n||6\n|| 2002\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| ''[[Idiot (2002 film)|Idiot]]''\n| {{Yes}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| Telugu\n| Remake of ''[[Appu (2002 film)|Appu]]''\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n||7\n|| 2003\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| ''[[Amma Nanna O Tamila Ammayi]]''\n| {{Yes}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| {{Yes}}\n| {